snippet.textDisplay:
Alex,
I really think you need to address the obvious mental illnesses that Cheryl has in your next video, and how Cheryl and Toni's relationship is actually REALLY toxic and destructive.
Both of Cheryl's parents were abusive and hated her for being a lesbian. Then her brother dies and Cheryl has to keep up this charade of being the most popular girl in school. A bunch of terrible things happen and she hates herself until finally she finds someone who actually seems to care about her. Toni actually asks Cheryl how she's doing and sees right through the whole mean girl act that she puts on. The whole entire thing about Cheryl and Toni was that Cheryl could be herself around Toni and didn't have to be a bitch and act strong. Then the writers decide to just go RUIN it all by making Cheryl act like an insufferable diva in every scene she's in. Cheryl obviously still have a lot of issues and she needs help, she lives alone in a mansion with two babies, her sick grandma, her girlfriend and a fucking corpse in a wheelchair. She's should be put in a literal mental institution like her creepy uncle suggested.


Toni starts out being this badass serpent who gives zero fucks and helps Jughead fit in. She turns out to be a really nice person too and she wants to help Cheryl because Cheryl doesn't have anyone else. Then Cheryl becomes a diva again and treats Toni like shit at times and Toni just goes along with it?! Because that's definitely not what she'd do when she was introduced to us.
Now in season 4 she's living with two babies, a sick grandma and her possessive, mentally ill girlfriend who brings her dead brother's corpse with her everywhere she goes.
I just feel so freaking bad for Toni, like just imagine the pressure she must be in, running that entire household. She has to take care of everyone in the house and doesn't have any time to take care of herself. In season three when she moved in she thought they were moving too fast but when she told Cheryl about it Cheryl full out flipped. Toni came running back to the house and now she's stuck taking care of two babies as well. She tried to get someone to help them but Cheryl wouldn't allow it and Toni doesn't dare to do anything about it. She knows if she goes against Cheryl, Cheryl will flip again.


I'm pretty sure Toni is staying around only because she's terrified of what Cheryl will do without her. Toni is the only good thing in Cheryl's life and if Cheryl didn't have Toni, Cheryl would literally go crazy, or even try to kill herself again. She's stuck in this destructing, toxic relationship that requires so much of her, she has to take care of two babies, a sick old crazy lady and her mentally ill girlfriend. She still has school that she needs to attend and she always has to think about making Cheryl upset, probably always worrying. There's also apparently a ghost in the house now that they have to find a way to deal with. It's freaking crazy how she hasn't had a mental breakdown already but she definitely should soon.
Of course, the show would never address this fact deal with it and they probably don't even realize how serious this is.

snippet.textDisplay:
Riverdale - Season 51.5:

It’s been five years since the apocalypse. Ever since JELLYBEAN has taken control of Riverdale, it’s in chaos. Jughead is stuck in a vortex in his mind and he is lost in his mind - supposedly - forever. Archie has began to fall in love with Veronica’s mother (Hemroids) but he can never confess.
Betty has died, ever since Alice had ate her black wig after taking these special pills called Its a Holly Jolly Christmas, that is being manufactured by Jughead because now he serves Jellybean: The Savior of Mankind. But, Betty isn’t really dead. Her dead body was fake, and she is now hanging out with a group of alien mischiefs that saved her. They rob people and do some crime stuff. Veronica is missing for most of the season, presumably, she learned Archie’s dark truth and ran off. Archie’s dark truth is that Veronica’s dad is his biological dad as well. But, Veronica was one of the aliens all along and the plot twist at the end is revealing herself to Betty. And Betty learns that in their alien language, “Daddy” means “Fuck my life.” Which Betty responded with, “Makes sense.” Jellybean ends up falling off her tower, Jughead had pushed her off, but Jellybean landed on trash bags and ran away. Jughead kills himself from going crazy. Archie marries Hemroids but learns that she is also an alien and divorces her. The ending shows Jellybean staring at Jughead— who ended up living because through a special cult ritual, Cheryl, who was gone on a summer trip most of the season, gives him the “kiss of life” She sees him through a window as she plans her next move, and behind her, her good old friend Asshat (who is an old Serpent member) is with her.
